parameters: \N<Deli>Vice Captain... I apologize for taking up your time.

\N<Seno>It's fine, but why call me out to a place like this? What do
you want with me?

\N<Seno>You're not being clear. You're a man, aren't you? Get it
together.
\N<Deli>I've been... admiring you for a long time...

\N<Deli>I know it's bothersome to hear something like this. I knew
that...
\N<Deli>But... I thought nothing would change unless I said it...

\N<Seno>Hehe, I'm happy to hear that. You're right, if you don't act
without fear, nothing will change. In that sense, you're
correct, and you have courage.
\N<Seno>But... sorry. You know I have a husband, right?

\N<Seno>But... it's been a while since I've felt this way, so I'm
truly happy.

\N<Seno>By the way... I saw this. You've been selected for the
personnel of that strategy, haven't you?

\N<Seno>It's a dangerous mission that goes deep into the heart of
Ryuda. But at the same time, it's a crucial mission for the
country.

\N<Seno>The higher-ups believe you can do it, that's why you were
chosen. Make sure to... do a good job, okay?

\N<Deli>...Could you please take a look at this? It's the order for
the operation we discussed.
\N<Seno>I see... So the day of your departure has been decided.

\N<Deli>Vice-Captain, about that time... I'm sorry. As you said, I
think I was a bit flustered.

\N<Deli>And... I'm grateful that you kept silent about what happened
then to everyone.

\N<Deli>I was... about to stray from the path. Even though I knew I
shouldn't do that in front of the person I admire, I
couldn't control myself.

\N<Deli>That's why... I'm truly grateful for what you said that day.
It may sound strange, but... it became a good memory in the
end.

\N<Deli>With this, I have no more doubts. I am... happy to
participate in this operation.
\N<Deli>...That's all I wanted to say. So...
\N<Seno>What are you doing talking and agreeing with yourself?

\N<Seno>As your superior officer, and as a human being, do you think
I can just silently send off a subordinate who looks like
they're heading to their death without a care?
\N<Seno>...Just this once, okay? And that's really it.

\N<Seno>And it's a promise. You absolutely must not take it
seriously, okay?

\N<Seno>Of course, it goes without saying that this is between us.
Can you promise that...?

\N<Dawn Soldier>It's about... the record of military achievements for the
recent mission. Please review it.

\N<Dawn Soldier>Yes, about that... those who lost their lives in this
mission...

\N<Seno>Heh... "It became a good memory," huh? Never thought they'd
actually become a memory.

\N<Seno>No matter how splendid the military achievements, if they
don't come back, it's all for nothing. Can't even raise a
toast in celebration.
That's why... I like strong men.
Because then, one less sad thing in my life will happen.
Because they won't die before me...
